{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 4 presents the comparative performance in all methods.",
    "Fine-tuning achieves the best performance, with accuracies of 91% and 80% on the DAIR-AI Emotion and SWMH datasets.",
    "Notably, zero-shot prompting emerged as the second-best performing approach, reaching 49% and 68% on each dataset, surpassing both the few-shot prompting and RAG.",
    "This suggests that carefully crafted prompts can effectively leverage the model's pre-trained knowledge for mental health text analysis, even without additional examples or context.",
    "However, we should clarify that in this study, we only used simple prompts as in the example shown in section 3.4 and kept them consistent throughout all experiments."
  ]
}